Physics interpretation:
  - Stricter cut (lower z_cut) counts more splittings, raises <n_SD>
    for both classes, but also lowers per-splitting gluon-vs-quark
    Casimir leverage -> AUC may not improve much.
  - Non-zero beta (angle-dependent grooming) tightens the cut at
    small angles and loosens it at large ones -> counts fewer
    splittings and can approach the Cambridge/Aachen ungroomed
    limit as beta -> large.
